entries.title: Soccer Pass
entries.notes: Mason is in U6 soccer.  He has scored 4 or 5 goals already and he's one of the better players on the field.  When he came off he said "I got 2 goals!"   So I said to him that McKenna would probably love to get a goal too. And maybe Mason could be a good teammate and pass her the ball next shift.   Well, the next shift Mason carried the ball the entire way from his end to the opposite teams net and was just about to kick it in.  Then he stopped and waited for McKenna to catch up and stepped out of the way so she could kick the ball in the net.   That may have been my proudest moment as a mom yet.  What a sweetheart that kid is.

entries.title: Phone Situation

Suddenly out of the backseat Mason pipes up "don't you think you should tell her about the phone situation?" entries.title: I Wanna Have Lots Of babies
entries.notes: Putting coop to be tonight.  I asked him if he was excited to be 5 and excited for his birthday party.  He said "yeah I can't wait to have babies".  Ah, what?   So I asked him when and he said "when I get older I want lots of babies".

entries.title: I Can Talk To Him For You
entries.notes: It was a rushed morning.  Mom was running around cleaning b/c we had another showing that day (5th one of the week).  Mom was tired of cleaning up in the morning and it was playoff hockey so dad was helping by getting the kids fed and ready but he also let them watch their iPads to check highlights.  Mom was frustrated and frazzled and muttering under her breathe.  Anyways, mom got the kids into the car and dad left for work.   As we were going I said "thanks for your help this morning.  Sorry for how stressed mom is but with these showings it makes for a rushed morning".  And Mason says "is it because dad doesn't help in the mornings?"   Mom said "well dad did help this morning.  He folded laundry and stuff." And Mason said "I can talk to him if you want?"   Lol. Always looking after him mom.

entries.title: Ackward Questions
entries.notes: So in subway on the weekend, out of the blue, Mason asked where babies come from.  Then tonight he told me that Cooper hit him in the private parts.  Then he got a thoughtful look on his face and said "do girls have private parts?"   I thought Rel was going to die laughing.
